The value of $p(1.5)$ is an integer. What is it?

solution:
$5x^2+9x-18$ can be written as $(5x-6)(x+3)$. Because $x$ must be positive, the only factor that can be considered is $(5x-6)$. Therefore: \begin{align*}
5x-6&=0\\
5x&=6\\
x&=\boxed{\frac{6}{5}}
\end{align*}

